FBIS3-17693 "drsov060_s_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 Georgia Abkhazia: Georgian Troops `Routed' LD2803191494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1637 GMT 28 Mar 94 LD2803191494 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Georgian armed formation that stayed in the mountains in Gulripsha region, Abkhazia "has been routed and no longer threatens the Abkhazian capital Sukhumi." The statement was made in a Monday interview with Interfax by the Abkhazian Defence Minister Sultan Sosnaliev. At the Abkhazian Defence Ministry Interfax was told that Georgian troops are besieged in Azhara community in the mountains. Abkhazian forces also control the Kodor canyon.
